## 📘 Problem Statement

Develop a web-based application using **Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB** to manage student records. The application should perform all database operations using Node.js and Express.js only.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

### a) Database Creation
Create a MongoDB database named `student`.

### b) Collection Creation
Create a collection named `studentmarks`.

### c) Insert Data
Insert an array of student documents into the collection. Each document should contain the following fields:
- Name  
- Roll_No  
- WAD_Marks  
- CC_Marks  
- DSBDA_Marks  
- CNS_Marks  
- AI_Marks  

### d) Display Records
Display all student documents and the total count of documents in the browser.

### e) Filter (DSBDA > 20)
Display the names of students who have scored more than 20 marks in the DSBDA subject.

### f) Update Records
Update the marks of specified students by incrementing each subject mark by 10.

### g) Filter (All Subjects > 25)
Display the names of students who have scored more than 25 marks in all subjects.

### h) Filter (WAD & CC < 40)
Display the names of students who have scored less than 40 marks in both WAD and CC subjects.

### i) Delete Record
Remove a specified student document from the collection.

### j) Tabular Display
Display all student data in the browser in a tabular format.

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Node.js  
- Express.js  
- MongoDB  
- Mongoose  
- EJS  

---

## 📌 Expected Outcome
- Perform CRUD operations on student records  
- Apply filtering conditions on data  
- Display results in browser  
- Show data in structured tabular format  